Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202022%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-technology-end-of-coding-software-developers-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20blowing%20everyone's%20minds%2C%20Kenji%20didn't%20really%20get%20it.%20Sure%2C%20it%20did%20some%20pretty%20cool%20things.%20But%20so%20had%20plenty%20of%20other%20generative%20AI%20models%20he'd%20tinkered%20with%20over%20the%20years.%20What%20so%20many%20outsiders%20thought%20was%20a%20world-changing%20breakthrough%20seemed%20to%20him%2C%20a%20machine%20learning%20engineer%2C%20much%20closer%20to%20an%20incremental%20improvement.%20All%20the%20fear%20that%20AI%20would%20swallow%20up%20everyone's%20jobs%20felt%20overblown.%20He%20certainly%20didn't%20think%20it%20could%20do%20%3Cem%3Ehis%3C%2Fem%3E%20job%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20though%2C%20he%20began%20to%20feel%20less%20sure.%20The%20AI%20tools%20he%20was%20using%20in%20his%20work%20at%20Block%2C%20the%20payments%20processor%20formerly%20known%20as%20Square%2C%20were%20becoming%20so%20good%20that%20he%20found%20himself%20delegating%20more%20and%20more%20of%20his%20coding%20and%20analysis%20to%20them.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%20you%20look%20around%20and%20say%2C%20'Gosh%2C%20I'm%20not%20doing%20that%20much%20of%20the%20work%20anymore%2C%20am%20I%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20Still%2C%20he%20believed%20his%20human%20mind%20had%20an%20edge%3A%20He%20understood%20the%20broader%20context%20necessary%20to%20ask%20the%20right%20questions.%20Besides%2C%20he%20was%20in%20a%20role%20that%20was%20close%20to%20the%20money%2C%20and%20businesses%20rarely%20cut%20those%20kinds%20of%20positions.%20%26quot%3BIt%20certainly%20dawned%20on%20me%20that%20I%20could%20be%20in%20line%20for%20redundancy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20didn't%20think%20I%20was%20quite%20there%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Kenji%20was%20among%20the%20more%20than%204%2C000%20employees%20who%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-layoffs-jack-dorsey-gratitude-meeting-employee-reaction-ai-integration-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%20at%20Block%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20this%20wasn't%20just%20your%20run-of-the-mill%20restructuring.%20Block%20was%20culling%20nearly%20half%20its%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20an%20astonishing%20move%20for%20a%20company%20that%20isn't%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20bankruptcy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20CEO%2C%20Jack%20Dorsey%2C%20left%20no%20room%20for%20interpretation%20about%20why.%20%26quot%3BIntelligence%20tools%20have%20changed%20what%20it%20means%20to%20build%20and%20run%20a%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Dorsey%20told%20investors.%20%26quot%3BA%20significantly%20smaller%20team%2C%20using%20the%20tools%20we're%20building%2C%20can%20do%20more%20and%20do%20it%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20ominous%20line%20in%20Dorsey's%20letter%20came%20toward%20the%20end%3A%20%26quot%3BWithin%20the%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20the%20majority%20of%20companies%20will%20reach%20the%20same%20conclusion%20and%20make%20similar%20structural%20changes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Dorsey%20is%20right%2C%20white-collar%20professionals%20are%20facing%20a%20stark%20future%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20Kenji%20had%20the%20misfortune%20of%20entering%20first.%20What%20he%20sees%20now%20from%20the%20other%20side%20feels%20instructive.%20The%20day%20after%20his%20layoff%2C%20he%20spoke%20with%20me%20on%20the%20condition%20that%20I%20not%20use%20his%20real%20name%20to%20avoid%20jeopardizing%20his%20future%20job%20prospects.%20I%20expected%20him%20to%20be%20angry%20or%20at%20least%20bewildered.%20Instead%2C%20he%20was%20almost%20Zen-like%20in%20his%20reflections%2C%20clear-eyed%20and%20calm.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20the%20first%2030%20seconds%20of%20%3Cem%3Eholy%20shit%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%2C%20as%20I%20read%20the%20whole%20thing%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20I%20get%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20Kenji%20may%20have%20been%20so%20quick%20to%20understand%20is%20that%20he's%20had%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20tech's%20cycle%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatgpt-replace-jobs-unemployment-salaries-technology-economist-daron-acemoglu-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautomation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20years.%20As%20a%20machine%20learning%20engineer%20at%20Block%2C%20Kenji%20built%20systems%20to%20detect%20fraud%20automatically%20%E2%80%94%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20shift%20in%20finance%20that%20has%20reduced%20the%20need%20for%20humans%20to%20review%20transactions%20for%20signs%20of%20suspicious%20activity.%20Block%20employs%20a%20team%20that%20reviews%20a%20small%20sample%20of%20transactions%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20models%20are%20flagging%20the%20right%20cases.%20Kenji%20understood%20that%20the%20better%20those%20models%20got%2C%20the%20fewer%20people%20would%20be%20needed%20to%20check%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20something%20unsettling%20about%20the%20reality%20that%20someone%20whose%20work%20helped%20automate%20other%20people's%20jobs%20was%20now%20being%20automated%20himself.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20standard%20advice%20was%20simple%3A%20Become%20the%20automator%2C%20lest%20you%20become%20automated.%20Five%20years%20ago%2C%20machine%20learning%20engineering%20was%20%3Cem%3Ethe%3C%2Fem%3E%20future-proof%20career%20%E2%80%94%20the%20apex%20predator%20of%20all%20occupations%20%E2%80%94%20until%2C%20suddenly%2C%20it%20wasn't.%20Large%20language%20models%20became%20the%20hot%20new%20thing%2C%20relegating%20traditional%20machine%20learning%20to%20yesterday's%20breakthrough.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20feel%20a%20little%20bit%20like%20a%20horse%20and%20buggy%20in%20the%20age%20of%20the%20automobile%2C%26quot%3B%20Kenji%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20face%20of%20disruption%2C%20Kenji%20did%20what%20any%20good%20technologist%20would%20do%3A%20He%20embraced%20the%20new%20tech.%20For%20more%20than%20a%20year%2C%20Dorsey%20had%20urged%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-ai-adoption-non-technical-software-engineer-performance-review-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eincorporate%20AI%20into%20their%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Kenji%20became%20a%20power%20user%20of%20Block's%20homegrown%20AI%20tools%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-afterpay-square-open-source-ai-agent-anthropic-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egoose%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20g2%2C%20as%20well%20as%20third-party%20ones%20like%20Claude%20and%20Cursor.%20That%20didn't%20protect%20him.%20If%20anything%2C%20he%20wonders%20whether%20it%20contributed%20to%20his%20job%20loss.%20%26quot%3BOver%20the%20last%20year%20that%20we%20were%20strongly%20encouraged%20to%20use%20all%20these%20AI%20tools%2C%20we%20were%20laying%20the%20foundations%20for%20our%20own%20replacement%2C%26quot%3B%20Kenji%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20show%20the%20tool%20how%20to%20do%20a%20task%20once%20or%20twice%2C%20it%20can%20kind%20of%20take%20it%20from%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20now%20is%20whether%20there%20will%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20Kenjis%20in%20the%20months%20ahead.%20Dorsey%20and%20plenty%20of%20industry%20executives%20clearly%20think%20so.%20Since%20last%20week's%20announcement%2C%20though%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2026-03-01%2Fjack-dorsey-s-4-000-job-cuts-at-block-arouse-suspicions-of-ai-washing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritics%20have%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Block%20may%20have%20simply%20overhired%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Maybe%20this%20wasn't%20AI%20making%20it%20possible%20to%20halve%20the%20workforce%20so%20much%20as%20a%20company%20correcting%20a%20bloated%20headcount.%20AI%2C%20in%20that%20telling%2C%20was%20merely%20the%20excuse%2C%20not%20the%20underlying%20cause%20of%20such%20sweeping%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sense%20is%20that%20more%20companies%20will%20follow%2C%20as%20Dorsey%20predicted%20%E2%80%94%20just%20not%20as%20quickly%20as%20he%20suggests.%20As%20I%20wrote%20last%20year%2C%20startups%20building%20from%20scratch%20in%20today's%20AI%20age%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-biggest-employers-facing-great-shrinking-corporations-ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoperating%20with%20dramatically%20leaner%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20not%20hard%20to%20imagine%20large%20companies%20eventually%20getting%20there%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Googles%20and%20the%20Amazons%20of%20the%20world%20have%20entrenched%20workflows%2C%20team%20structures%2C%20and%20job%20descriptions%20they'll%20need%20to%20redesign%20around%20AI%2C%20and%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hype-hasnt-changed-work-yet-bosses-employees-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoverhaul%20will%20take%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20more%20likely%20scenario%20is%20that%20layoffs%20come%20in%20waves%20over%20several%20years%2C%20alongside%20persistently%20low%20hiring%2C%20steadily%20shrinking%20companies'%20headcounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20Kenji%20plans%20to%20take%20a%20break%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20sizable%20severance%20Block%20offered%20him%20(the%20company%20offered%20laid-off%20employees%20at%20least%2020%20weeks%20of%20pay%2C%20with%20an%20additional%20week%20of%20pay%20for%20every%20year%20of%20tenure).%20Then%2C%20he'll%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-job-search-white-collar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elooking%20for%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20enough%20knowledge%2C%20enough%20context%2C%20enough%20connections%20that%20I'm%20quite%20confident%20I%20could%20land%20another%20job%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Machine%20learning%20might%20not%20be%20the%20hot%20new%20thing%20it%20was%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20in%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20longer%20term%20is%20a%20different%20story.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20land%20a%20job%20tomorrow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20zero%20confidence%20that%20it%2C%20too%2C%20couldn't%20be%20automated%20away%20in%20a%20couple%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-secure-job-in-tech-block-layoffs-ai-warning-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772701741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8c7dfd3e2f1aef36a03ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-secure-job-in-tech-block-layoffs-ai-warning-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20talked%20to%20one%20of%20the%20laid-off%20Block%20employees.%20He%20gave%20me%20a%20sobering%20warning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-secure-job-in-tech-block-layoffs-ai-warning-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Day%205%20Of%20Security%20Curbs%20In%20Kashmir%20After%20Protests%20Against%20Khamenei's%20Killing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Security%20restrictions%20continue%20to%20remain%20imposed%20in%20Kashmir%20to%20prevent%20protests%20over%20killing%20of%20Iran's%20supreme%20leader%20Ay