kumar-to-resign-as-bihar-cm-contest-rajya-sabha-election-126030500361_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fnitish-kumar-to-resign-as-bihar-cm-contest-rajya-sabha-election-126030500361_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fnitish-kumar-to-resign-as-bihar-cm-contest-rajya-sabha-election-126030500361_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20oil%20price%20spike%20won't%20fix%20Russia's%20strained%20finances%2C%20an%20analyst%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224991%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia's%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8f47dd3e2f1aef36a04a8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223372%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHigher%20oil%20prices%20typically%20boost%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20budget%2C%20which%20helps%20finance%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3ESergei%20Fadeichev%2FPool%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMiddle%20East%20conflict%20sends%20oil%20higher%20amid%20fears%20over%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20supply%20risks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESanctions%2C%20discounts%2C%20and%20a%20strong%20ruble%20blunt%20the%20boost%20to%20Russia's%20oil%20revenue.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20analyst%20warns%20Moscow's%20budget%20strain%20will%20persist%20without%20sustained%20higher%20prices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOil%20prices%20have%20surged%20after%20fresh%20conflict%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20raised%20fears%20of%20supply%20disruptions%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-strikes-middle-east-shipping-air-cargo-freight-impact-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStrait%20of%20Hormuz%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20that%20would%20normally%20be%20a%20windfall%20for%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20time%2C%20it%20may%20not%20be%20enough%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20current%20temporary%20spike%2C%20filtered%20through%20sanctions%20discounts%20and%20an%20unfavorable%20exchange%20rate%2C%20is%20unlikely%20to%20change%20the%20fundamental%20arithmetic%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Alexander%20Kolyandr%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%2C%20in%20a%20Wednesday%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInternational%20benchmark%20Brent%20crude%20and%20US%20West%20Texas%20Intermediate%20were%20more%20than%203%25%20higher%2C%20trading%20around%20%2484%20and%20%2477.50%20per%20barrel%20respectively%20late%20on%20Wednesday.%20Both%20grades%20are%20around%2035%25%20higher%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20energy%20exporters%2C%20and%20its%20federal%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20and%20by%20extension%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20relies%20heavily%20on%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Moscow%20does%20not%20receive%20international%20benchmark%20prices%20for%20its%20crude.%20Its%20Urals%20oil%20trades%20at%20a%20sanctions-driven%20discount%2C%20and%20the%20strong%20ruble%20means%20each%20dollar%20of%20oil%20revenue%20converts%20into%20fewer%20rubles%20for%20the%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Brent%20above%20%2480%20does%20not%20automatically%20deliver%20the%20revenue%20Russia%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOil%20and%20gas%20revenues%20plunged%2050%25%20in%20January%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20falling%20to%20levels%20last%20seen%20during%20the%20pandemic%20shock%20in%202020.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20federal%20budget%20ran%20a%20deficit%20of%201.72%20trillion%20rubles%20%E2%80%94%20about%200.7%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20according%20to%20Russian%20Finance%20Ministry%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnless%20oil%20prices%20stay%20higher%20for%20longer%20and%20the%20ruble%20weakens%20significantly%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-putin-orders-more-taxes-wartime-gdp-growth-slows-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKremlin's%20budget%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20here%20to%20stay%2C%26quot%3B%20Kolyandr%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKolyandr's%20analysis%20comes%20as%20investors%20weigh%20whether%20the%20latest%20Middle%20East%20escalation%20will%20trigger%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-prices-iran-strait-hormuz-disruption-storage-crude-output-risk-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esustained%20oil%20shock%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20particularly%20for%20Asian%20countries%20that%20are%20reliant%20on%20heavily%20reliant%20on%20Middle%20Eastern%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20India%20%E2%80%94%20now%20two%20of%20the%20biggest%20buyers%20of%20Russian%20crude%20%E2%80%94%20still%20source%20a%20large%20share%20of%20their%20oil%20from%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20leaving%20both%20exposed%20to%20disruptions%20in%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20prolonged%20disruption%20in%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20could%20shift%20trade%20flows%2C%20potentially%20increasing%20scrutiny%20on%20whether%20Asian%20importers%20turn%20further%20to%20discounted%20Russian%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-oil-price-iran-war-energy-supply-shock-gold-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMarkets%20have%20been%20volatile%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20US%20and%20Israeli%20attacks%20on%20Iran%20over%20the%20weekend.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20stocks%20in%20Asia%20slumped%20on%20energy%20security%20fears%20before%20rebounding%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-iran-war-oil-price-spike-impact-kremlin-finances-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772691072000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8f512fd